<h2 id="appendix-a-verifying-your-keepassxc-download-without-using-the-command-line">Appendix A: Verifying Your KeePassXC Download Without Using The Command Line</h2>

<p>You should follow these steps <em>after</em> downloading the KeePassXC dmg file, but <em>before</em> you install it. KeePassXCâ€™s official site now has <a href="https://keepassxc.org/verifying-signatures">pretty good instructions too</a>.</p>

<h3 id="1-download-gpg-suite">1. Download GPG Suite</h3>

<p>Letâ€™s head over to <a href="https://gpgtools.org/">gpgtools.org</a>. At the time of this writing, thereâ€™s a beta version of this software called â€œGPG Suite 2017.1â€ and a regular version of â€œGPG Suiteâ€. If youâ€™re running macOS Sierra (10.12) or higher, Iâ€™d advise you go with the beta version. If youâ€™re running an older version of macOS (10.11 or earlier), you should be good with the not beta version.</p>

<p>After downloading the proper version of GPG Suite, install it as you would any other Mac application. The GPG Suite website provides <a href="https://gpgtools.tenderapp.com/kb/how-to/how-to-verify-the-downloaded-gpg-suite">a guide to verifying your GPG Suite download, as well as any downloaded file</a>.</p>

<h3 id="2-download-and-import-the-keepassxc-gpg-public-master-key">2. Download and Import the KeePassXC GPG Public Master Key</h3>

<p>Once GPG Suite is installed, go to <a href="https://keepassxc.org/verifying-signatures">the KeePassXC page on verifying downloads</a>.</p>

<p>Weâ€™re looking to download and import KeePassXCâ€™s public master key, which should be below the heading â€œImporting the Public Master Keyâ€. One way to do this is to find the link in the sentence â€œManual download from our website and import with gpgâ€. Right-click (or control + click on Mac) the link and select â€œSave Link Asâ€¦â€ and save it to your Downloads folder.</p>

<p><img src="/img/keepassxc/save-master-key-as.png" alt="Download KeePassXC Master Public Key" /></p>

<p>Now open a program called â€œGPG Keychainâ€ (it should be part of the GPG Suite we installed earlier). In the top-left, click the â€œImportâ€ button and select the master public key file you just downloaded.</p>

<p>If you successfully imported the key, you should get a message to that effect.</p>

<h3 id="3-crosscheck-the-public-master-key-you-downloaded">3. Crosscheck the Public Master Key You Downloaded</h3>

<p>Now, if the KeePassXC website is compromised, this public key could be compromised as well. To mitigate this risk, weâ€™re going to crosscheck the key you downloaded with other sources. Another one of these sources is <a href="https://twitter.com/KeePassXC">KeePassXCâ€™s Twitter account</a>: the developers should have a pinned tweet that contains whatâ€™s called a â€œfingerprintâ€ of their master key, or at least the last 16 characters of the fingerprint.</p>

<p>In GPG Tools, double-click the â€œKeePassXC Releaseâ€ key. In the sidebar that pops up, look for the fingerprint of the key you downloaded â€“ it should be 40 characters spaced out in 4-character segments. The last 16 characters of it should match the 16 characters in the pinned tweet exactly.</p>

<p>Another source is <a href="https://github.com/keepassxreboot/keepassxreboot.github.io">the Github repository of the KeePassXC website</a>. The key fingerprint should be displayed somewhere around <a href="https://github.com/keepassxreboot/keepassxreboot.github.io/blob/master/verifying-signatures.html#L86">line 86 of this page</a>.</p>

<p>Once youâ€™re satisfied that you downloaded and imported the actual key, change the â€œOwnertrustâ€ setting to â€œUltimateâ€, via the dropdown menu.</p>

<p><img src="/img/keepassxc/ultimate-trust-dropdown.png" alt="Ultimate trust" /></p>

<h3 id="4-download-the-gpg-signature-of-your-keepassxc-release">4. Download the GPG signature of your KeePassXC Release</h3>

<p>Now, letâ€™s head back over to <a href="https://keepassxc.org/download">the KeePassXC download page</a>. Click the â€œmacOSâ€ tab if itâ€™s not already highlighted and then click the link called â€œGPG signatureâ€. Save this file to your Downloads file, where you downloaded the KeePassXC dmg file earlier. Itâ€™s important that theyâ€™re in the same folder (this folder is likely the Downloads folder).</p>

<p><img src="/img/keepassxc/signature-same-folder.png" alt="Signature next to DMG" /></p>

<h3 id="5-verifying-your-download">5. Verifying your Download</h3>

<p>Now, right-click the .dmg file and go to Services &gt; â€œOpenPGP: Validateâ€. You should get a pop up that says â€œSigned by: KeePassXC Release <a href="mailto:release@keepassxc.org">release@keepassxc.org</a>â€ and then a â€œkey IDâ€ in parentheses. For us, whatâ€™s critical is that you see â€œultimate trustâ€ printed at the end of the line. If you do, youâ€™re good!</p>

<p><img src="/img/keepassxc/signed-ultimate-trust.png" alt="Ultimate trust" /></p>

